oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Park Owen Grocery
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Park Hanner Owen Sr. (1879-1961) and Edmond Garrett Collier (1884-1937) standing outside of Park Owen Grocery located on Main Street in Mount Pleasant. A sign above the store reads "Park Owen staple & fancy groceries / Highest cash price paid for country produce." Handwriting on the photograph identifies the men and year.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Grocery stores; Storefronts; Men
